Are you or your organisation a US Person (defined below) or located in the United States:


NO, I am not and my organisation is not a US Person* or located in the United States



Yes, I am or my organisation is either a US Person* or located in the United States.




*A "US Person" means:

any natural person resident in the United States ("US"); or
any corporation, partnership, limited liability company or other organisation incorporated or organised in the US, but excluding an offshore branch or agency of a US person that operates for valid business reasons and is engaged and regulated as an insurance company or bank; or
a branch or agency of a foreign entity located in the US; or
a trust of which the trustee is a US person, unless a non-US person has or shares investment discretion and no beneficiary (and no settlor if the trust is revocable) is a US person; or
an estate of which a US person is the executor or administrator, unless the estate is governed by foreign law and a non-US person has or shares investment discretion; or
a non-discretionary account or similar account (other than an estate or trust) held by a  dealer or other fiduciary for the benefit of a US person; or
a discretionary account or similar account (other than an estate or trust) held by a dealer or other fiduciary organised, incorporated, or (if an individual) resident in the United States, unless held for the benefit of a non-US person; or
any entity organised under the laws of a foreign jurisdiction and formed by a US Person principally for the purpose of purchasing securities not registered in the United States; or
any entity organised or incorporated for the purposes of evading US securities laws




