Help


Fund centre


				The Fund centre is your access point for fund fact sheets and other key fund information.
			

				The fund list can be filtered by product type using the first set of tabs (Pensions unit-linked DB and DC, Open-ended investment company and SICAV).
			

				The fund list can be filtered further by using the keyword search and the drop down menus (asset class, dealing, strategy, currency, domicile).
			

				Selecting a category from a drop down menu will automatically refresh the remaining categories, leaving only relevant options to choose from.
			

				Once you have applied all relevant filters, select the ‘Filter funds’ button to generate your new fund list.
			

				To clear all filters, click on the ‘Clear filters’ button. Please note, this cannot be undone. You will need to re-filter the fund list again once cleared.
			

Your shortlist


				You can create your own fund shortlist which will be remembered on subsequent visits to our site.
			

				The ability to remember your list is dependent on using cookies. If you have disabled
				cookies, the shortlist will not be saved. Find out more about cookies in the next
				section or visit the Cookie policy section of this website. You will find this in the footer 
				of any page of the site.
			

				You will need to create your own shortlist of funds in order to use our interactive tools – Portfolio builder and Fund comparison.
			

				The shortlist can contain as many or as few products as you wish, however, the
				number of funds that can be displayed within the tools is limited. Fund comparison
				can take a maximum of six funds, while Portfolio builder can take 10.
			

				You can clear your shortlist by clicking on the ‘Clear shortlist’ link to the right of the
				‘Launch funds in…' buttons. Please note, this cannot be undone. You will need to 
				build your shortlist again once cleared. 
			

Cookies


				Cookies are small text files that are placed on your device by websites that you visit.
				They are widely used in order to make websites work, or work more efficiently.
			

				The Fund centre cookie is required to remember your shortlist. It is categorised as a
				functionality cookie. It is persistent and will only be removed if you choose to remove
				all cookies.
			

				Without the Fund centre cookie, the shortlist will not be remembered. Find out more
				about cookies in the Cookie policy section of this website. You will find this in the 
				footer of any page of the site.
			

Keyword search tool


				The keyword search functionality is the first field within the list of filters. Enter one
				or more keywords and click the ‘Filter funds’ button. This should return a list of funds 
				relating to the search terms you have entered.
			

				The tool searches fund names and fund codes. It also searches partial fund names.
			

				The results will appear in alphabetical order (as per the fund list itself) and will not be 
				ranked according to relevance.
			

				If you have already filtered the fund list using the drop down menus at the top of the
				page, only the filtered list will be searched.
			

				Please be as accurate and specific as you can when entering your search terms in 
				order to return the most relevant results.
			

Portfolio builder


				This interactive tool allows you to create, view and manipulate a virtual portfolio of up to 10 funds.
			

				First, create your shortlist in the Fund centre. 
			

				Once you have created your shortlist, click on the blue button that reads ‘Launch funds in Portfolio builder’.
			

				You will be taken to a page which prompts you to set the weights of each fund in your
				portfolio. You can do this manually, or you can simply click on ‘Set equal weights’ and 
				the tool will do it for you.
			

				At this point, you can either view your online portfolio, or generate a PDF.
			

				Once in your online portfolio, you can click on any category’s percentage value to drill down for further information.
			

Fund comparison


				This interactive tool allows you to view and compare fund metrics for up to six funds.
			

				First, create your shortlist in the Fund centre. 
			

				Once you have created your shortlist, click on the blue button that reads ‘Launch funds in Fund comparison’.
			

				Once in the tool, you can generate and save a PDF.
			

				You can remove products via the shortlist at the top of the page.
			

				The data accurate date, and intended audience for each product, appears at the top of the Fund comparison list.
			

Prices


				To view fund prices, click on the relevant fund type tab. Prices are not available under the ‘View all’ tab.
			

				If you have any problems viewing fund prices or have any queries, please contact us. 
				Contact information can be found in the Contact us section of the website.
			

Fund charges


				Fund charges are listed under the Charges tab within the Fund centre. If you have 
				any queries about charges, please contact us.
			








